@node FEATURES "Key Features"

   · Integrated HTML editor and viewer allows easy switch between edit and view mode:
      · Very fast parsing
      · Very fast image loading
      · Supports lots of HTML things
   · Supports localization (of cooz)
   · Uses MUI
   · 100% written in assembler (puh!!)
@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

   · AmigaOS 3.0 or better
   · MUI 3.8
   · AFAIR NList.mcc, NListview.mcc, BetterBalance.mcc, ToolBar.mcc, BetterString.mcc,
     TearOffBay.mcc, TearOffPanel, TextEditor.mcc and HTMLview.mcc.
     Go to www.amiga.dk/tumult and download!
@endnode
@node HISTORY "History of Voimariini"

Version 1.04 (17. May 1999):
----------------------------

   · FIXED: bugs
   · NEW: allows quite easy way to edit multiple docs
   · NEW: some bugs, see @{"BUGS" LINK BUGS} section.

   (Never released)

Version 1.07 (1. July 1999):
----------------------------

   · FIXED: many bugs, many bugs are still going to be fixed
   · NEW: now uses tearoffbay.mcc and tearoffpanel.mcc
   · NEW: improved lots of thigs

Version 1.08 (3. July 1999):
----------------------------

   · FIXED: stupid requester couldn't remember directory and file name
   · FIXED: Voimariini was asking to save file even if it was already saved
   · FIXED: HTML view wasn't always updated
   · FIXED: something, can't remember anymore
   · NEW: now accepts file name in command line
   · NEW: french locale, thanks to Jerome Chesnot

   · PLUS: some minor enhancements
@endnode
@node BUGS "Known Bugs"

   · With multiple windows Voimariini may freeze sometimes. If this happens send a
     signal #31 for Voimariini process to activate exit routine (use Executive's
     Commander or something similar). Don't open more than four editor/view windows!
   · GUI layout is not remembered
   · Voimariini doesn't view text-files or other non-html files
   · Your HTML code must be bug free or you can't see it in HTML view
   · Anchors doesn't work always
   · Use the most recent version of Toolbar.mcc!

@endnode
